```python id=bloq
from qualtran.bloqs.qft.qft_text_book import QFTTextBook
bloq = QFTTextBook(bitsize=3, with_reverse=True)
```
```python id=golden
import numpy as np
N = 8
i = np.arange(N).reshape(N, 1)
j = np.arange(N).reshape(1, N)
golden = np.exp(2j * np.pi * (i * j) / N) / np.sqrt(N)
golden = golden.astype(complex)   # shape (8,8), analytic DFT
```
